                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.5151/174: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 7, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your 93, October 5, 4 p.m., and Consulate General’s October 5, 6 [<hi
                        rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m.<note n="37" xml:id="d767fn37">Latter not
                        printed.</note> In view of possible conflicts of interests between the
                    American groups known to be actively interested in reaching an exchange
                    agreement with Argentina, and between them and holders of Argentine bonds, the
                    Department is confident that you will exercise care not to give the impression
                    that this Government favors any particular group or is in any way involved in
                    the negotiations of these private groups.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
